    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "medium",
    "text": "Now we replace the model $\\hat{\\mathbf{z}}_{t-1} = \\mathbf{f}_{t}[\\mathbf{z}_{t},\\phi_{t}]$ with a new model $\\hat{\\boldsymbol{\\epsilon}} = \\mathbf{g}_{t}[\\mathbf{z}_{t},\\phi_{t}]$, which predicts the noise $\\boldsymbol{\\epsilon}$ that was mixed with $\\mathbf{x}$ to create $\\mathbf{z}_{t}$:"
